  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Electrical velocimetry (EV) is one of the latest adaptions of impedance cardiography showing
      diverging results. With electrode position being a suspected factor influencing measurement
      accuracy or reproducibility for impedance cardiography in general, no data is currently
      available on altering the gap of the two lower electrodes in EV. Reference values were
      determined using the non-invasive gold-standard cardiac magnetic resonance imaging (CMR).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
